# QUICK REFERENCE — WHAT NOT TO BUILD
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ❌ FastAPI routes, APIRouter, app factories          → chassis (contract 1)
# ❌ Middleware for tenant resolution, auth, CORS       → chassis (contract 3)
# ❌ Logging/structlog configuration                   → chassis (contract 4)
# ❌ Prometheus metrics setup                          → chassis (contract 4)
# ❌ Dockerfile, docker-compose, CI/CD pipelines       → l9-template (contract 5)
# ❌ Terraform modules, k8s manifests                  → l9-template (contract 5)
# ❌ Custom request/response schemas for HTTP          → universal contract envelope (contract 1)
# ❌ Manual packet creation without .derive()          → packet protocol (contract 8)
# ❌ String-interpolated Cypher without sanitize_label → security (contract 9)
# ❌ Post-filter matching in Python                    → gate-then-score in Cypher (contract 13)
# ❌ Hardcoded GDS algorithm scheduling                → declarative spec (contract 19)
# ❌ Cross-tenant KGE embeddings                       → domain isolation (contract 20)
# ❌ eval(), exec(), pickle.load()                     → banned patterns (contract 9)
# ❌ yaml.load() without SafeLoader                    → banned patterns (contract 9)
# ❌ Raw httpx/requests calls to other nodes           → delegation protocol (contract 8)
# ❌ Direct INSERT into packetstore/memory_embeddings  → memory substrate (contract 7)
# ❌ Redefining PacketEnvelope/TenantContext/ExecuteRequest → shared models (contract 7)
# ❌ raise NotImplementedError (ship code or defer)    → zero-stub protocol
# ❌ TODO / PLACEHOLDER comments without DEFERRED.md   → zero-stub protocol


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# RUFF CONFIG (pyproject.toml reference — do not contradict)
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#
# Global ignores (legitimately inapplicable to this project):
#   E501     → formatter handles line length
#   TRY003   → long exception messages acceptable in domain code
#   TRY400   → logging.error vs logging.exception — both acceptable
#   TRY004   → TypeError vs ValueError — overly prescriptive
#   TC001    → typing-only first-party import — breaks Pydantic v2 validators at runtime
#   TC003    → typing-only stdlib import — same runtime issue
#   ARG001-3 → unused function/method/classmethod args — handler interface compliance
#   ARG005   → unused lambda args — callback signature compliance
#   SIM105   → contextlib.suppress — explicit try/except is clearer in async+structlog code
#   B007     → unused loop variable — use _ prefix convention
#   PLC0206  → dict index missing items — false positives with dynamic dicts
#
# Threshold raises (configure limits, don't ignore):
#   PLR0913  → max-args = 8       (default 5 is too low for audit/compliance APIs)
#   PLR0912  → max-branches = 15  (default 12 is too low for gate compiler validation)
#   PLR0911  → max-returns = 8    (default 6 is too low for tool dispatch)
#
# Per-file ignores (scoped to specific directories):
#   tests/**  → PLR2004 (magic values), PT011 (broad raises), E741 (short var names)
#   engine/config/** → PLR2004 (magic values in defaults)
#   tools/**  → PLC0415 (lazy imports), E741 (short var names)
